"v.偏离，转向 【英】 v. 偏离，转向(to turn to one side; bend; swerve) 【记】 de+flect(弯曲)→弯 到旁边→偏离 【同】 同根词：reflection( 反射)；flexible(灵 活的) v. 偏离; 使转向 = bend = swerve 【记】flect弯曲－弯到一边－偏离 【参】reflection(n 反射; 沉思); flexible(adj 灵活的) 【记】flect 弯曲 bend；flex 弯曲 【相关】flex 弯曲， flexible 易弯曲的 灵活的，deflect 偏转，inflect 弯曲，reflect,reflex 反射 deflect (v.)  1550s, from Latin deflectere ""to bend (something) aside or downward,"" from de- ""away"" (see de-) + flectere ""to bend"" (see flexible). Originally transitive, the intransitive sense is first recorded 1640s. Related: Deflected; deflecting."
